{
  "texts": [
    "This paper investigates LLM comparative assessment, a simple zero-shot approach to NLG evaluation.",
    "We demonstrate that for moderately sized LLMs, comparative assessment outperforms absolute scoring, and is an effective automatic assessment, achieving near state-of-the-art performance for a range of NLG evaluation tasks.",
    "Furthermore, we show that LLMs are prone to have positional bias that could impact their decisions, however, we introduce a simple debiasing approach that leads to performance boosts, especially for biased systems.",
    "Computational Cost.",
    "The comparative assessment framework with the full set of comparisons uses"
  ]
}